## Implementation Details

The Analytics component is integrated into the root layout (`app/layout.js`), which means:
- Analytics tracking is enabled across all pages
- Page view events are automatically tracked for all routes
- No additional configuration needed in child pages or components

## Next Steps for Deployment

To enable data collection, ensure Web Analytics is enabled in your Vercel dashboard:
1. Go to your project settings in Vercel
2. Navigate to the Analytics tab
3. Enable Web Analytics
4. Deploy your application

Once deployed to Vercel, the Analytics component will automatically begin collecting visitor and page view data.

## Notes

- The integration is framework-aware and will automatically handle Next.js routing
- Analytics tracking only activates when deployed to Vercel (no local tracking)
- No environment variables or additional configuration required
- The implementation follows Vercel's official best practices for Next.js App Router
